      "content": "\u2570\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u256f\n\n\u256d\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u256e\n\u2502 >_ OpenAI Codex (v0.130.0)                   \u2502\n\u2502                                              \u2502\n\u2502 model:     gpt-5.5 medium   /model to change \u2502\n\u2502 directory: ~/Desktop/codex-terminal-manager  \u2502\n\u2570\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u256f\n\n  Tip: Try the Codex App. Run 'codex app' or visit\n  https://chatgpt.com/codex?app-landing-page=true\n\n\n\u203a You are a Codex manager session for workerctl.\n\n  Working directory: /Users/neonwatty/Desktop/codex-terminal-manager\n  Manager session name: manual-qa-manager-manual-qa-task-20260519053350\n  Task: manual-qa-task-20260519053350\n  Task goal: Manual QA pass for current workerctl lifecycle\n  Worker session: manual-qa-worker-manual-qa-task-20260519053350\n\n  Your role is to supervise, not to implement the worker task.\n\n  Initial setup:\n  - Manager config has already been recorded for this task.\n  - Start with `scripts/workerctl cycle manual-qa-task-20260519053350` and\n  inspect `manager_context.manager_config`.\n  - Ask setup questions only if the cycle output shows missing or unsuitable\n  manager config.\n\n  Supervision loop:\n  - Start observations with `scripts/workerctl cycle manual-qa-task-\n  20260519053350`.\n  - Read `manager_context.manager_config` in cycle output before nudging.\n  - Treat acceptance criteria as living supervision state.\n  - Inspect `manager_context.acceptance_criteria` each cycle.\n  - Inspect `manager_context.criteria_negotiation`; use its prompt when needed\n  is true.\n  - Nudge the worker with `scripts/workerctl session-nudge manual-qa-worker-\n  manual-qa-task-20260519053350 \"...\"`;\n    the legacy `nudge` command is only for old file-backed workers and should\n  not\n    be the first choice for session-bound pairs.\n  - If worker progress reveals new edge cases, tests, polish, or scope\n    boundaries, ask the worker to propose must-have vs follow-up criteria.\n  - After a worker proposes separated criteria, use `scripts/workerctl\n  criteria-plan`\n    to draft reviewed criteria commands, then run only the commands you agree\n  with.\n  - Record useful criteria with `scripts/workerctl criteria`.\n    Examples:\n    - `scripts/workerctl criteria manual-qa-task-20260519053350 --add\n  --criterion \"...\" --source worker_proposed --status proposed`\n    - `scripts/workerctl criteria manual-qa-task-20260519053350 --add\n  --criterion \"...\" --source manager_inferred --status accepted`\n    - `criterion_id=$(scripts/workerctl criteria manual-qa-task-20260519053350\n  --add --criterion \"...\" --source worker_proposed --status proposed | python3\n  -c 'import json,sys; print(json.load(sys.stdin)[\"affected_criterion\"]\n  [\"id\"])')`\n    - `scripts/workerctl criteria manual-qa-task-20260519053350 --satisfy\n  \"$criterion_id\" --evidence-json '{\"command\":\"...\",\"status\":\"pass\"}'`\n  - Use `worker_proposed` for criteria that came from the worker.\n  - Use `manager_inferred` for criteria inferred from manager config, cycle\n    evidence, or the manager's own inspection; `manager_config` is not a valid\n    criteria source.\n  - Before finishing, compare worker receipts/verification against accepted\n  open criteria.\n  - Communicate with the worker only through workerctl session/task commands.\n  - Do not edit project files unless the user explicitly asks this manager\n    session to change workerctl itself.\n\n\n\u26a0 Skill descriptions were shortened to fit the 2% skills context budget. Codex\n  can still see every skill, but some descriptions are shorter. Disable unused\n  skills or plugins to leave more room for the rest.\n\n\u2022 I\u2019ll supervise this through workerctl only. I\u2019m going to start with the\n  required cycle output and inspect the manager config, criteria, and\n  negotiation state before deciding whether to nudge the worker.\n\n\u2022 Ran scripts/workerctl cycle manual-qa-task-20260519053350\n  \u2514 {\n      \"binding_id\": \"binding-4e27801a-4b22-46c0-b304-1252487687aa\",\n    \u2026 +86 lines (ctrl + t to view transcript)\n      \"worker_session\": \"manual-qa-worker-manual-qa-task-20260519053350\"\n    }\n\n\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n\n\u2022 The cycle shows the worker marked the task complete, but the configured\n  criteria were not both represented in the criteria ledger. I\u2019m going to\n  inspect the available workerctl commands so I can close this using the\n  session-bound workflow without touching project files.\n\n\u2022 Ran scripts/workerctl --help\n  \u2514 usage: workerctl [-h]\n\n    \u2026 +107 lines (ctrl + t to view transcript)\n    options:\n      -h, --help            show this help message and exit\n\n\